    <notes>Established in 1900 to formalize British control over Northern Nigeria, which primarily
        involved bringing the Fulani Empire under British control, but also the remnants of the
        Bornu Empire in what is today northeastern Nigeria. Bornu came peaceably under British
        sovereignty around 1900, apparently through diplomatic means (military force was not
        used).</notes>
